<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Atriplex</i> <i>prostrata</i> or <i>Cotula</i> <i>coronopifolia</i> are dominant or co-dominate together in the herbaceous layer with <i>Bolboschoenus</i> <i>maritimus</i>, <i>Chenopodium</i> <i>foliosum</i>, <i>Distichlis</i> <i>spicata</i>, <i>Polypogon</i> <i>monspeliensis</i> and/or <i>Sesuvium</i> <i>verrucosum</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1 m; cover is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Atriplex prostrata</i> > 40% relative cover in the herbaceous layer with other non-natives (Keeler-Wolf and Vaghti 2000).</li>
		
		<li><i>Atriplex prostrata</i> > 60% relative cover in the herbaceous layer, or co-dominant with <i>Chenopodium foliosum</i> or <i>Cotula coronopifolia</i> (Pickart 2006, Sikes et al. 2021).</li>
		
		<li><i>Cotula coronopifolia</i> > 60% relative cover in herbaceous layer, or co-dominant with <i>Sesuvium verrucosum</i> (Keeler-Wolf and Vaghti 2000).</li>
		
		<li><i>Cotula coronopifolia</i> > 60% relative cover in the herbaceous layer (Pickart 2006, Buck-Diaz et al. 2021).</li>
		
		<li><i>Cotula coronopifolia, Polypogon monspeliensis</i>, and/or <i>Atriplex prostrata</i> > 50% relative cover in the herbaceous layer (Buck-Diaz et al. 2021).</li>
		
		<li><i>Cotula coronopifolia</i> and/or <i>Atriplex prostrata</i> > 50% relative cover in the herbaceous layer (Sikes et al. 2021).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Seasonally flooded saline mudflats, brackish marshes. Soils are alluvium. The USACE Wetland Inventory (2018 national list) recognizes <i>Cotula coronopifolia</i> as an OBL plant and <i>Atriplex prostrata</i> as a FAC plant. </div>
</div>

        
